The Coalition of Northern Yoruba Youths (CNYY), has recommended Reverend Yakubu Pam to the presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, for consideration as his running mate. The group, in a communiqué issued at the end of its executive meeting in Kaduna, noted that going by Tinubu’s pedigree and political antecedents, having Rev. Pam on a joint ticket will further consolidate and brighten his chances of winning the election. 2023: APC former delegates ask court to stop Tinubu from replacing Masari Nigeria has no reason not to conduct census – UNFPA The communiqué, which was jointly signed by the group’s chairman and secretary, Deji Abdullateef and Ajayi Johnson, respectively, said the combination of the two would lead APC to victory come February 25, 2023. 